snippet.title: The latest from the TensorFlow channel
snippet.description:
TensorFlow Dev Summit 2018 - March 30, 2018
The Computer History Museum, Mountain View, CA 
Join us for the livestream (Keynote starts on March 30th 2018 at 9:30 AM PDT) âž” https://goo.gl/EakyW1


Learn more here: https://www.tensorflow.org/dev-summit/
Follow TensorFlow on Twitter: https://twitter.com/tensorflow

TensorFlow Dev Summit brings together a diverse mix of machine learning users from around the world for a full day of highly technical talks, demos, and conversation with the TensorFlow team and community. At this point, we are unable to accept new applications, but welcome you to join our waiting list, in case a spot opens up for the in-person event. Please note that we will be livestreaming and recording all talks. They will be available on the TensorFlow Youtube channel & you can check the TensorFlow website and @tensorflow for updates.

snippet.title: Integrating the Google Assistant with Embedded Devices
snippet.description:
Learn more about integrating your own hardware devices with the Google Assistant. This video series covers how to embed the Google Assistant SDK into custom hardware projects, and using the Smart Home API to control your own devices.

When you are done, join our Google+ community to keep up to date and share information with other developers at https://g.co/actionsdev

Learn more from the documentation at our developer sites:
